'''毅力号'''（{{lang-en|Perseverance}}）是由[[美国国家航空航天局|美国国家航空航天局]]下属的[[喷气推进实验室|喷气推进实验室]]制造，用于[[火星2020|火星2020]]任务中的[[火星车|火星车]]。该探测器已于美国东部时间2020年7月30日上午7:50（世界协调时11:50）发射<ref>{{Cite web|title=Launch Windows|url=https://mars.nasa.gov/mars2020/timeline/launch/launch-windows/|accessdate=2020-07-31|last=mars.nasa.gov|work=mars.nasa.gov|language=en|archive-date=2020-07-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200731081243/https://mars.nasa.gov/mars2020/timeline/launch/launch-windows/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，於美国加利福尼亚时间2021年2月18日下午3时55分成功登陆火星，並降落在[[耶澤羅撞擊坑|耶澤羅撞擊坑]]<ref>{{Cite web|title=Perseverance rover has successfully landed on Mars and sent back its first images|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2021/02/18/world/mars-perseverance-rover-landing-scn-trnd/index.html|accessdate=2021-02-18|language=en|archive-date=2021-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415021308/https://edition.cnn.com/2021/02/18/world/mars-perseverance-rover-landing-scn-trnd/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Photos: NASA Prepares to Launch the Mars Rover Perseverance - The Atlantic|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/photo/2020/07/photos-nasa-prepares-to-launch-the-mars-rover-perseverance/614716/|accessdate=2020-07-31|last=Taylor|first=Alan|work=www.theatlantic.com|language=en|archive-date=2020-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919230226/https://www.theatlantic.com/photo/2020/07/photos-nasa-prepares-to-launch-the-mars-rover-perseverance/614716/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。同年3月5日，毅力号在火星上完成首次行驶测试<ref>{{cite news |title=美国“毅力”号火星车完成着陆后首次行驶测试 |url=http://finance.eastmoney.com/a/202103061833170874.html |accessdate=2021-03-06 |archive-date=2021-03-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210324091057/http://finance.eastmoney.com/a/202103061833170874.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。毅力号的外观与[[好奇號|好奇号]]大致上相同，携带 7 种科学仪器，23 个攝影鏡頭，两个麦克风。任务计划探测[[耶澤羅撞擊坑|耶澤羅撞擊坑]]附近的火星表面。毅力号还携带了一台名为[[机智号|机智号]]的无人机，配合毅力号进行科学研究。2021年4月20日，毅力号成功将[[火星大气|火星大气]]的[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]转化成[[氧|氧]]，這是地球以外的首次造氧<ref>{{cite news |title=毅力号火星上造氧 地球以外第一次 |url=https://www.rfi.fr/cn/%E6%AF%85%E5%8A%9B%E5%8F%B7%E7%81%AB%E6%98%9F%E4%B8%8A%E9%80%A0%E6%B0%A7-%E5%9C%B0%E7%90%83%E4%BB%A5%E5%A4%96%E7%AC%AC%E4%B8%80%E6%AC%A1}}</ref>。2021年9月6日，毅力號成功取得第一塊火星岩石樣本。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cna.com.tw/news/ait/202109070119.aspx|title=毅力號取得第一塊火星岩石樣本 NASA：重大成就|author=中央通訊社|accessdate=2021-09-07|archive-date=2021-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211009011701/https://www.cna.com.tw/news/ait/202109070119.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 设计 ==
[[好奇號|好奇号]]工程团队帮助设计了毅力号，因此两者外观相似<ref>{{Cite web|title=NASA announces plans for new $1.5 billion Mars rover|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/nasa-announces-plans-for-new-1-5-billion-mars-rover/|accessdate=2020-07-31|last=Harwood|first=William|work=CNET|language=en|archive-date=2018-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143942/https://www.cnet.com/news/nasa-announces-plans-for-new-1-5-billion-mars-rover/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=NASA to Launch New Mars Rover in 2020|url=https://www.space.com/18763-nasa-new-mars-rover-2020.html|accessdate=2020-07-31|last=December 2012|first=Mike Wall 04|work=Space.com|language=en|archive-date=2021-03-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210324091112/https://www.space.com/18763-nasa-new-mars-rover-2020.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。不过工程师们重新设计了毅力号的轮子，使其更坚固，避免出现好奇号轮子破损的情形。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Curiosity wheel damage: The problem and solutions|url=https://www.planetary.org/articles/08190630-curiosity-wheel-damage|accessdate=2020-07-31|work=The Planetary Society|language=en|archive-date=2020-05-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200526153804/https://www.planetary.org/blogs/emily-lakdawalla/2014/08190630-curiosity-wheel-damage.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>毅力号的铝制轮子更厚、更耐用，并减小了宽度，增大了直径（52.5 厘米（20.7 英寸）），相比好奇号 50 厘米（20 英寸）的轮子更重。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mars 2020 rover receives upgraded eyesight for tricky skycrane landing|url=https://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2016/10/mars-2020-rover-eyesight-skycrane-landing/|accessdate=2020-07-31|date=2016-10-11|work=NASASpaceFlight.com|language=en-US|archive-date=2020-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201206084129/https://www.nasaspaceflight.com/2016/10/mars-2020-rover-eyesight-skycrane-landing/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title="Mars 2020 – Body: New Wheels for Mars 2020".|url=https://mars.nasa.gov/mars2020/spacecraft/rover/body/|accessdate=|author=NASA/JPL. Retrieved|date=2018-07-06|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2019-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726133551/https://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/mars2020/mission/rover/body/|dead-url=no}}</ref>铝制轮子上覆盖着用于牵引的夹板和用于提供弹簧支撑的弧形钛辐条。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Rover Wheels|url=https://mars.nasa.gov/mars2020/spacecraft/rover/wheels/|accessdate=2020-07-31|last=mars.nasa.gov|work=mars.nasa.gov|language=en|archive-date=2021-03-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210324091059/https://mars.nasa.gov/mars2020/spacecraft/rover/wheels/|dead-url=no}}</ref>毅力号携带了更大的仪器套件、新的采样和缓存系统以及改装后的轮子，这使得它比前辈好奇号重了 17%（好奇号为 899 千克，而毅力号为 1050 千克）。此外，毅力号还装有一个长 2.1 米（6 英尺 11 英寸）的五关节机械臂，机械臂上配备了取芯钻，该设备可以定位在火星车前方的任何位置以采集岩石样本。

原本作为好奇号备用装置的[[多任务放射性同位素热电发生器|多任务放射性同位素热电发生器]](MMRTG)将会作为驱动毅力号的动力。<ref>{{Cite web|title=NASA plans 2020 Mars rover remake|url=http://cosmiclog.nbcnews.com/_news/2012/12/04/15678579-nasa-plans-2020-mars-rover-remake|accessdate=2020-08-04|last=Log|first=Cosmic|work=NBC News|language=en|archive-date=2015-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150227001036/http://cosmiclog.nbcnews.com/_news/2012/12/04/15678579-nasa-plans-2020-mars-rover-remake|dead-url=yes}}</ref>毅力号的发电机质量为 45 公斤（99 磅），使用 4.8 公斤（10.6 磅）的二氧化钚作为稳定供应的热源，转化产生电能。该发电机能够产生约 110 瓦的电能，预计任务期间将会保持该水平。 此外，毅力号还携带两个锂离子充电电池在闲时储能，用于满足暂时超过 MMRTG 的稳定电力输出水平时的峰值需求。MMRTG 由美国能源部提供给 NASA ，能够提供了 14 年的工作寿命。 与太阳能电池板不同，MMRTG 为工程师提供了极大的灵活性，即使在夜间，沙尘暴期间或者冬季都能够提供稳定的电源，方便工程师们操作毅力号上的科学仪器。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mars 2020 Rover Tech Specs|url=https://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/mars2020/mission/rover/electrical-power/|accessdate=|author=JPL/NASA. Retrieved|date=2018-07-06|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2019-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726133536/https://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/mars2020/mission/rover/electrical-power/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

毅力号的计算机使用 BAE RAD750 辐射硬化单板计算机。車載CPU是一顆經過輻射強化的PowerPC，與iMac G3同款處理器<ref>https://chinese.engadget.com/nasa-perseverance-powerpc-750-010046656.html</ref>。该计算机包含 128 兆字节的易失性 DRAM，运行频率为 133 兆赫。飞行控制软件能够在一个单独的卡上访问 4 千兆字节的 NAND 非易失性存储器。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Prototyping an Onboard Scheduler for the Mars 2020 Rover|url=https://ai.jpl.nasa.gov/public/documents/papers/rabideau_iwpss2017_prototyping.pdf|accessdate=|author=|date=|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2021-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210218172828/https://ai.jpl.nasa.gov/public/documents/papers/rabideau_iwpss2017_prototyping.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

作为 “[[火星2020|火星2020]]”计划的一部分，与 “毅力号” 同行的还有名为 “小机灵” 的实验无人机。这是一架质量为 1.8 公斤（4.0 磅）的太阳能无人机，将用于测试飞行稳定性以及提供预期 30 天的毅力号勘察最佳行驶路线规划任务。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mars Helicopter to Fly on NASA’s Next Red Planet Rover Mission|url=http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/mars-helicopter-to-fly-on-nasa-s-next-red-planet-rover-mission|accessdate=2020-08-01|date=2018-05-11|last=Northon|first=Karen|work=NASA|archive-date=2021-04-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210410091800/https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/mars-helicopter-to-fly-on-nasa-s-next-red-planet-rover-mission/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 除了相机外，它没有携带任何科学仪器。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Nasa prepares tiny chopper for Mars flight|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-49512101|newspaper=BBC News|date=2019-08-29|accessdate=2020-08-01|language=en-GB|first=Jonathan|last=Amos|archive-date=2020-12-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201205134102/https://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-49512101|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=A Helicopter on Mars? NASA Wants to Try|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/11/science/mars-helicopter-nasa.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2018-05-11|accessdate=2020-08-01|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Kenneth|last=Chang|archive-date=2018-05-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180512130422/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/11/science/mars-helicopter-nasa.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=NASA is sending a helicopter to Mars to get a bird’s-eye view of the planet|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/5/11/17346414/nasa-mars-2020-helicopter-atmosphere|accessdate=2020-08-01|date=2018-05-11|last=Grush|first=Loren|work=The Verge|language=en|archive-date=2020-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201206232523/https://www.theverge.com/2018/5/11/17346414/nasa-mars-2020-helicopter-atmosphere|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 仪器 ==
