基于毅力号的任务目标，初期提出了 60 余项仪器用于评估<ref>{{Cite web|title=NASA Receives Mars 2020 Rover Instrument Proposals for Evaluation|url=http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=4017|accessdate=2020-08-02|work=NASA/JPL|archive-date=2020-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202170356/https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=4017|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=NASA announces the instruments for the next Mars rover|url=https://arstechnica.com/science/2014/07/nasa-announces-the-instruments-for-the-next-mars-rover/|accessdate=2020-08-02|date=2014-07-31|last=Timmer|first=John|work=Ars Technica|language=en-us|archive-date=2015-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150120210008/http://arstechnica.com/science/2014/07/nasa-announces-the-instruments-for-the-next-mars-rover/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2014年7月31日，美国宇航局宣布了毅力号将携带的七项科学仪器。<ref>{{Cite web|title=NASA Announces Mars 2020 Rover Payload to Explore the Red Planet|url=http://www.nasa.gov/press/2014/july/nasa-announces-mars-2020-rover-payload-to-explore-the-red-planet-as-never-before|accessdate=2020-08-02|date=2015-04-15|last=Beutel|first=Allard|work=NASA|archive-date=2021-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210219071458/https://www.nasa.gov/press/2014/july/nasa-announces-mars-2020-rover-payload-to-explore-the-red-planet-as-never-before/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=NASA Announces Mars 2020 Rover Payload to Explore the Red Planet as Never Before|url=http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/mars2020/news/whatsnew/index.cfm?FuseAction=ShowNews&NewsID=1678|accessdate=|author=Brown, Dwayne|date=2014-07-31|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2016-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305012957/http://mars.jpl.nasa.gov/mars2020/news/whatsnew/index.cfm?FuseAction=ShowNews&NewsID=1678|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

* X射线岩石化学行星仪（PIXL），这是一台[[X射线|X射线]][[荧光光谱|荧光光谱仪]]，用于确定火星表面物质的细微元素成分。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Mars 2020 Rover's PIXL to Focus X-Rays on Tiny Targets|url=http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=4237|accessdate=2020-08-02|work=NASA/JPL|archive-date=2020-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919232651/https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=4237|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Wayback Machine|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808034737/http://www.davidraythompson.com/publications/Thompson_2014_iSAIRAS_PIXL.pdf|accessdate=2020-08-02|date=2014-08-08|work=web.archive.org}}</ref>
* 火星地下实验雷达成像仪（RIMFAX），这是一个穿地雷达，用于对不同的地面密度、结构层、埋藏的岩石、陨石进行成像，并探测 10 米（33 英尺）深的地下水冰和咸盐水。RIMFAX 由挪威国防研究机构（FFI）提供。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Radar Imager for Mars' Subsurface Exploration (RIMFAX)|url=https://mars.nasa.gov/mars2020/spacecraft/instruments/rimfax/|accessdate=2020-08-02|last=mars.nasa.gov|work=mars.nasa.gov|language=en|archive-date=2019-12-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191222000204/https://mars.nasa.gov/mars2020/mission/instruments/rimfax/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Mars 2020 rover's RIMFAX radar will 'see' deep underground|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/mars-2020-rover-s-rimfax-radar-will-see-deep-underground-1.2739698|accessdate=|author=Chung, Emily|date=2014-08-19|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2020-09-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200925083325/https://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/mars-2020-rover-s-rimfax-radar-will-see-deep-underground-1.2739698|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=U of T scientist to play key role on Mars 2020 Rover Mission|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/mars-2020-rover-s-rimfax-radar-will-see-deep-underground-1.2739698|accessdate=|author=|date=|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2020-09-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200925083325/https://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/mars-2020-rover-s-rimfax-radar-will-see-deep-underground-1.2739698|dead-url=no}}</ref>
* 火星环境动态分析仪（MEDA），用于测量温度、风速、风向、压力、相对湿度、辐射以及尘埃颗粒大小和形状。它由西班牙天体生物学中心提供。<ref>{{Cite web|title=In-Situ Resource Utilization (ISRU)|url=https://gcd.larc.nasa.gov/projects/in-situ-resource-utilization/|accessdate=|author=|date=2015-04-02|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2015-04-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402175156/https://gcd.larc.nasa.gov/projects/in-situ-resource-utilization/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>
* [[火星氧氣原位資源利用實驗|火星氧氣原位資源利用實驗]]（MOXIE），用于一项探索性技术研究：尝试从火星大气中的二氧化碳（<chem>CO2</chem>）中产生少量的氧气（<chem>O2</chem>）。这项技术未来可能扩大规模，用于人类生命支持，或为返回任务制作火箭燃料。<ref>{{Cite web|title=NASA TechPort|url=https://techport.nasa.gov/view/33080|accessdate=2020-08-02|work=techport.nasa.gov|language=en|archive-date=2020-10-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201017155217/https://techport.nasa.gov/view/33080|dead-url=no}}</ref>
* 超级相机（SuperCam），这是一套可以从远处对岩石和风化石进行成像、化学成分分析和矿物学分析的仪器。它是好奇号探测器上的 ChemCam 的升级版，配备了两台激光器和四台光谱仪，使它能够远程识别生物特征，评估火星过去的可居住性。洛斯阿拉莫斯国家实验室、法国天体物理学和行星学研究所（IRAP）、法国航天局（CNES）、夏威夷大学和西班牙巴利亚多利德大学合作开发和制造了SuperCam。<ref>{{Cite web|title=NASA Signs Agreements to Advance Journey to Mars|url=http://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-administrator-signs-agreements-to-advance-agencys-journey-to-mars|accessdate=2020-08-02|date=2015-06-16|last=Northon|first=Karen|work=NASA|archive-date=2020-12-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201201063857/https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-administrator-signs-agreements-to-advance-agencys-journey-to-mars/|dead-url=no}}</ref>
* Mastcam-Z相机，它可以像双筒望远镜一样变焦并创建全景和立体图像，同时还可以确定火星表面的矿物成分和绘制3D地图。
* 拉曼荧光光谱仪（SHERLOC），这是一种紫外线拉曼光谱仪，利用精细尺度的成像和紫外线（UV）激光来扫描环境中是否有宜居有机化合物。<ref>{{Cite web|title=SHERLOC to Micro-Map Mars Minerals and Carbon Rings|url=http://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=4238|accessdate=2020-08-02|work=NASA/JPL|archive-date=2020-09-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200920150254/https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=4238|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=SHERLOC: Scanning Habitable Environments with Raman and Luminescence for Organics and Chemicals, an Investigation for 2020|url=http://www.hou.usra.edu/meetings/georaman2014/pdf/5101.pdf|accessdate=|author=|date=|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2020-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200928094244/https://www.hou.usra.edu/meetings/georaman2014/pdf/5101.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

